+# Passkey Authentication - Dashboards Integration
+
+## Overview
+
+This document describes the passkey authentication integration for OpenSearch Dashboards.
+
+## Status
+
+🚧 **In Progress** - Core components created, integration pending
+
+## What's Been Created
+
+### 1. WebAuthn Helper Functions
+**File**: `public/utils/webauthn-helpers.ts`
+
+Utility functions for WebAuthn operations:
+- `base64urlDecode()` - Decode base64url to Uint8Array
+- `arrayBufferToBase64url()` - Encode ArrayBuffer to base64url
+- `isWebAuthnSupported()` - Check browser support
+- `isPlatformAuthenticatorAvailable()` - Check for Touch ID/Face ID/Windows Hello
+- `getWebAuthnErrorMessage()` - User-friendly error messages
+- `formatCredential()` - Format credentials for display
+
+### 2. Passkey Service
+**File**: `public/services/passkey-service.ts`
+
+Service class for all passkey API operations:
+- `getRegistrationOptions()` - Get registration challenge
+- `registerPasskey()` - Register new passkey
+- `getAuthenticationOptions()` - Get authentication challenge
+- `authenticateWithPasskey()` - Authenticate with passkey
+- `listPasskeys()` - List user's passkeys
+- `deletePasskey()` - Delete a passkey
+- `renamePasskey()` - Rename a passkey
+
+### 3. Passkey Login Button
+**File**: `public/apps/login/passkey-login-button.tsx`
+
+React component for passkey login:
+- "Sign in with Passkey" button
+- Username input modal
+- WebAuthn authentication flow
+- Error handling and loading states
+- Only shows if WebAuthn is supported
+
+## Integration Steps
+
+### Step 1: Add Passkey Button to Login Page
+
+Edit `public/apps/login/login-page.tsx`:
+
+```typescript
+import { PasskeyLoginButton } from './passkey-login-button';
+
+// In the formOptions function, after the basic auth section:
+if (authOpts.includes(AuthType.BASIC)) {
+  // ... existing basic auth code ...
+  
+  // Add passkey button
+  formBody.push(
+    <PasskeyLoginButton
+      http={props.http}
+      onSuccess={() => redirect(props.http.basePath.serverBasePath)}
+    />
+  );
+}
+```
+
+### Step 2: Add Passkey Management Page
+
+Create `public/apps/account/passkey-management.tsx`:
+
+```typescript
+import React, { useState, useEffect } from 'react';
+import {
+  EuiPage,
+  EuiPageBody,
+  EuiPageContent,
+  EuiPageContentHeader,
+  EuiPageContentHeaderSection,
+  EuiTitle,
+  EuiButton,
+  EuiBasicTable,
+  EuiButtonIcon,
+  EuiSpacer,
+} from '@elastic/eui';
+import { PasskeyService } from '../../services/passkey-service';
+import { formatCredential } from '../../utils/webauthn-helpers';
+
+export function PasskeyManagementPage({ http, username }) {
+  const [credentials, setCredentials] = useState([]);
+  const [isLoading, setIsLoading] = useState(true);
+  
+  const passkeyService = new PasskeyService(http);
+  
+  useEffect(() => {
+    loadCredentials();
+  }, []);
+  
+  const loadCredentials = async () => {
+    setIsLoading(true);
+    const creds = await passkeyService.listPasskeys(username);
+    setCredentials(creds.map(formatCredential));
+    setIsLoading(false);
+  };
+  
+  const handleDelete = async (id: string) => {
+    if (confirm('Are you sure you want to delete this passkey?')) {
+      await passkeyService.deletePasskey(id);
+      loadCredentials();
+    }
+  };
+  
+  const columns = [
+    {
+      field: 'friendlyName',
+      name: 'Name',
+    },
+    {
+      field: 'createdAtFormatted',
+      name: 'Created',
+    },
+    {
+      field: 'lastUsedAtFormatted',
+      name: 'Last Used',
+    },
+    {
+      name: 'Actions',
+      actions: [
+        {
+          name: 'Delete',
+          description: 'Delete this passkey',
+          icon: 'trash',
+          type: 'icon',
+          onClick: (item) => handleDelete(item.id),
+        },
+      ],
+    },
+  ];
+  
+  return (
+    <EuiPage>
+      <EuiPageBody>
+        <EuiPageContent>
+          <EuiPageContentHeader>
+            <EuiPageContentHeaderSection>
+              <EuiTitle>
+                <h2>Manage Passkeys</h2>
+              </EuiTitle>
+            </EuiPageContentHeaderSection>
+            <EuiPageContentHeaderSection>
+              <EuiButton onClick={() => {/* Open registration modal */}}>
+                Register New Passkey
+              </EuiButton>
+            </EuiPageContentHeaderSection>
+          </EuiPageContentHeader>
+          
+          <EuiSpacer />
+          
+          <EuiBasicTable
+            items={credentials}
+            columns={columns}
+            loading={isLoading}
+          />
+        </EuiPageContent>
+      </EuiPageBody>
+    </EuiPage>
+  );
+}
+```
+
+### Step 3: Add Route for Passkey Management
+
+Edit the account app router to add passkey management route.
+
+### Step 4: Update Configuration
+
+Add passkey configuration to `opensearch_dashboards.json` or config files:
+
+```json
+{
+  "passkey": {
+    "enabled": true
+  }
+}
+```
+
+## Testing
+
+### Manual Testing
+
+1. **Start OpenSearch** with security plugin and passkey enabled
+2. **Start Dashboards** in development mode:
+   ```bash
+   yarn start
+   ```
+3. **Navigate to login page**
+4. **Click "Sign in with Passkey"**
+5. **Enter username and authenticate**
+
+### Unit Tests
+
+Create `public/apps/login/test/passkey-login-button.test.tsx`:
+
+```typescript
+import { render, screen, fireEvent } from '@testing-library/react';
+import { PasskeyLoginButton } from '../passkey-login-button';
+
+describe('PasskeyLoginButton', () => {
+  it('renders button when WebAuthn is supported', () => {
+    // Mock WebAuthn support
+    global.PublicKeyCredential = {} as any;
+    
+    render(<PasskeyLoginButton http={mockHttp} onSuccess={jest.fn()} />);
+    
+    expect(screen.getByText('Sign in with Passkey')).toBeInTheDocument();
+  });
+  
+  it('does not render when WebAuthn is not supported', () => {
+    // Remove WebAuthn support
+    delete (global as any).PublicKeyCredential;
+    
+    render(<PasskeyLoginButton http={mockHttp} onSuccess={jest.fn()} />);
+    
+    expect(screen.queryByText('Sign in with Passkey')).not.toBeInTheDocument();
+  });
+});
+```
+
+## API Endpoints
+
+All endpoints are provided by the OpenSearch Security plugin:
+
+| Endpoint | Method | Purpose |
+|----------|--------|---------|
+| `/_plugins/_security/passkey/registration/options` | POST | Get registration challenge |
+| `/_plugins/_security/passkey/registration/verify` | POST | Verify and store credential |
+| `/_plugins/_security/passkey/authentication/options` | POST | Get authentication challenge |
+| `/_plugins/_security/passkey/authentication/verify` | POST | Verify assertion and login |
+| `/_plugins/_security/passkey/credentials/list` | POST | List user's passkeys |
+| `/_plugins/_security/passkey/credentials/{id}` | DELETE | Delete passkey |
+| `/_plugins/_security/passkey/credentials/{id}` | PUT | Update passkey metadata |
+
+## Browser Support
+
+Passkeys work in:
+- ✅ Chrome 67+
+- ✅ Firefox 60+
+- ✅ Safari 13+
+- ✅ Edge 18+
+
+The integration automatically detects support and hides the passkey button on unsupported browsers.
+
+## Security Considerations
+
+1. **Origin Validation**: All API calls include the Origin header
+2. **HTTPS Required**: WebAuthn only works on HTTPS (or localhost for development)
+3. **No Private Keys**: Only public keys are stored on the server
+4. **Session Management**: Successful authentication establishes a secure session
+
+## Next Steps
+
+1. ✅ Create helper functions
+2. ✅ Create passkey service
+3. ✅ Create login button component
+4. ⏳ Integrate login button into login page
+5. ⏳ Create passkey management page
+6. ⏳ Add registration flow
+7. ⏳ Add unit tests
+8. ⏳ Add E2E tests
+9. ⏳ Update documentation
+
+## Resources
+
+- Backend API: `../security/PASSKEY_AUTHENTICATION.md`
+- WebAuthn Guide: https://webauthn.guide/
+- MDN WebAuthn API: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Web_Authentication_API
+
+## Questions?
+
+See the backend documentation in the security plugin repository for API details and examples.
